# Elite Auth System Upgrade — Implementation Plan

## Current State Assessment

The project is a **split-architecture** app:
- **Client**: Next.js 16 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui + React 19  
- **Server**: Express.js + Mongoose + Redis + argon2 + Pino + OpenTelemetry

**Already in place** (substantial existing work):

| Area | What Exists |
|------|-------------|
| DB Models | 9 models: User, Session, AuthEvent, MfaConfig, OAuthAccount, Department, EmailVerification, PasswordReset, index |
| Auth Library | 7 files: tokens, sessions, passwords, rateLimit, riskEngine, audit, validations |
| Email | sender.ts + 2 templates (verify-email, reset-password) |
| Auth Components | LoginForm, RegisterForm, MFASetup, PasswordStrengthMeter, SessionsTable, OAuthButtons, SSOButton |
| Auth Pages | login, register, verify-email, forgot-password, reset-password, mfa, sessions |
| Middleware | Client: security headers + RBAC via jose; Server: authMiddleware, errorMiddleware, uploadMiddleware |
| CI/CD | ci.yml, security-audit.yml, deploy-staging.yml, deploy-production.yml + Gemini workflows |
| Docker | docker-compose.yml, docker-compose.prod.yml, .dockerignore, client/Dockerfile, server/Dockerfile |
| Docs | ONBOARDING.md, AUTH_ARCHITECTURE.md, INCIDENT_RESPONSE.md, SECURITY_CHECKLIST.md, REDIS_KEYS.md |
| Tests | 2 unit (passwords, tokens), 1 integration (auth), 1 load (k6), 1 setup |
| Scripts | generate-keys.ts, check-env.ts, seedAdmin.ts, seedCommunities.ts, seedFieldData.ts, seedStories.ts |

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Architecture Decision: Keep Split Architecture vs Migrate to Unified Next.js**
> 
> The spec calls for Next.js 14 API Routes. Your current project uses **Express as a separate backend** (Next.js 16 on the client). This plan **keeps the split Express + Next.js architecture** and upgrades within it, because:
> 1. Migrating all Express routes to Next.js API Routes is a full rewrite (~6000+ lines)
> 2. Your existing auth controller (524 lines) and middleware are Express-specific
> 3. The split architecture actually gives better horizontal scaling (separate server instances)
> 4. All spec features (MFA, CSRF, riskEngine, etc.) can be implemented identically on Express
>
> If you want to migrate to a unified Next.js 14 App Router instead, say so and I'll revise this plan.

> [!WARNING]
> **Next.js Version**: Your client uses **Next.js 16.1.1** (latest). The spec says Next.js 14. This plan keeps Next.js 16 since downgrading would be destructive. All features work the same way.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Scope**: This is a massive upgrade (~80+ files to create or modify). Estimated effort: 60–100 tool calls across multiple sessions. I recommend we proceed phase-by-phase, verifying each before moving on.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1 — MongoDB Schema Upgrades

Summary: Upgrade all 9 existing models to match the spec. Add missing fields, indexes, methods, and immutability guards.

---

#### [MODIFY] [User.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/src/lib/db/models/User.ts)
- Add fields: `fullName`, `avatarUrl`, `bannedReason`, `mustChangePwd`, rename `name` → `fullName`
- Add `studentId` (unique sparse index)
- Add instance methods: `isLocked()`, `incrementFailedAttempts()`, `resetFailedAttempts()`, `toSafeObject()`
- Add compound indexes: `{ departmentId, role }`

#### [MODIFY] [Session.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/src/lib/db/models/Session.ts)
- Add `tokenFamily` field for reuse detection
- Add typed `location` sub-document `{ country, city, region }`
- Add `deviceInfo.deviceType` enum constraint
- Add TTL index on `expiresAt` (`expireAfterSeconds: 0`)
- Add compound index `{ userId, tokenFamily }`

#### [MODIFY] [AuthEvent.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/src/lib/db/models/AuthEvent.ts)
- Add `riskScore` field (Number, nullable)
- Add immutability pre-hooks (disable `updateOne`, `updateMany`, `findOneAndUpdate`, `deleteOne`, `deleteMany`)
- Add compound index `{ userId: 1, createdAt: -1 }`
- Set `timestamps: { createdAt: true, updatedAt: false }`

#### [MODIFY] [Department.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/src/lib/db/models/Department.ts)
- Add `institutionDomain` field
- Add index on `institutionDomain`

