## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

**Existing tests** (verify nothing breaks):
```bash
cd server && npx vitest run
```
This runs the existing [passwords.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/tests/unit/passwords.test.ts) and [tokens.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/tests/unit/tokens.test.ts) + [auth.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL-IN/Desktop/Projects/Ethnography-research-project/server/tests/integration/auth.test.ts).

**After each phase**, run:
```bash
cd server && npx vitest run --reporter=verbose
```

**After Phase 8 (testing phase)**, run full suite with coverage:
```bash
cd server && npx vitest run --coverage
```

**Build verification** (client):
```bash
cd client && npm run build
```

**Lint check** (client):
```bash
cd client && npm run lint
```

### Manual Verification

After Phase 4 (Frontend):
1. Start both client and server locally
2. Open `http://localhost:3000/auth/login` — verify split-panel layout renders with navy/gold design
3. Open `http://localhost:3000/auth/register` — verify sectioned form, domain validation indicator
4. Test MFA setup flow visually at `/auth/mfa`

After Phase 7 (Docker):
1. Run `docker compose up -d` from project root
2. Verify all services start: `docker compose ps`
3. Check `http://localhost:8081` for mongo-express (if included)
4. Run `docker compose exec server npm run seed`

> [!TIP]
> I recommend we tackle this phase-by-phase. After approving this plan, tell me which phase to start with — or I'll begin with Phase 1 (schemas) since everything depends on it.
